  </p>

  <p><img src="/images/sunny_logo.svg" class="square_right" alt="sunny logo">
    As you can see, none of the photos in this section are actually happy. On is a logo that uses a sun-like form that seems like it might be quite happy and optimistic; one is a photograph of a happy looking, healthy (and fried egg-like) flower on a sunny day, while the third is a photo of a beach on a sunny day, which many people associate with happiness. <!--while the third are some words that make no literal sense (you can't walk on sunshine) but their shape and color is happy.-->So none of these things are actually pictures of happiness. But what is a picture of happiness? There isn't one, because it's different for all of us. This is why using references is so useful when talking about abstract concepts like happiness.
